    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="426"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 851.51/46</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-05T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2126. Secretary of the Treasury requests that you communicate with the Minister
                    of Finance and ascertain what amount of loan or credit in the United States
                    would prove most helpful to the French <pb facs="0594" n="520" xml:id="pg_520"/>
                    Government at this time to cover the period of say the next six months.
                    Ascertain, also, in what instalments the loan would likely be required, and also
                    to what extent the credit would be employed in the purchase of supplies in this
                    country. It should not be implied that the United States would condition the
                    loan upon its expenditure in the United States alone. The inquiry is made merely
                    to ascertain if the loan would be used here, because it has a bearing upon the
                    method of financing it. Prompt reply is desirable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For a statement by the British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs of the
                        Allies’ financial situation and needs, see the memorandum quoted in the
                        telegram from the Ambassador in Great Britain, No. 5949, April 6, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_11">page 11</ref>.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
